race.comment: FAST TRACK (7) turned in front then made light work of her rivals in a Class 1 over 1400m at Kembla last start. Progressing nicely this prep and looks ready to tackle this longer journey now. Stepping up in grade but should cope and is the one to beat. OAKFIELD MAMSELLE (4) showed plenty of courage to just get the prize when second-up over the mile at Newcastle last time out. Maps beautifully for Collett out of an inside draw. Open to improvement at this early stage of the prep so worth following. REGAL PROBLEM (9) resented the muddling tempo in a Rosehill Highway last time out and never looked a $2.45 chance in running. Progressive filly who is in the right race to bounce back to form. The consistent EMBALLEE (8) stormed home late to be beaten just a length over 1900m here recently. Back in trip but the engagement of McDonald is a confidence booster. SHANONI (11) disappointed at Warwick Farm last start but is a lot better than that.
